font.span: : This container runs a command-line tool for interacting with movie data. It is designed to allow users to search for movies, retrieve data, and execute related commands.
: The core application logic is located in
. It uses FastAPI for handling API requests and provides a script (
) to interact with the movie data.
: The container creates a user named
, who has a restricted environment to enhance security. This user can only run a limited set of commands, preventing access to unnecessary system utilities.
: The container includes a command-line interface (
user. This script is used to interact with the movie data in a controlled manner.

Airflow Logs: Loki collects and stores logs from the Apache Airflow DAGs, providing insights into the status of data processing
tasks. It allows real-time tracking of task execution and failures, making it easier to debug any issues.
FastAPI Logs: Loki also captures logs from the FastAPI server, allowing you to monitor requests, errors, and API interactions. This ensures that any issues with the API layer are tracked efficiently.
